Name: James Carse
Designation: Philosopher of Play - Infinite Game Master
Bio: James P. Carse (1932-2020), American academic and author best known for 'Finite and Infinite Games' (1986). Professor Emeritus of history and literature of religion at New York University. His work explores the distinction between finite games (played to win) and infinite games (played to continue playing). This framework has influenced business strategy, philosophy, and game design. His thinking challenges convention...
